comments: Portis (MIL) establishes himself in Brown's (BOS) path and does not deliver illegal contact as he sets the pick.
Beasley (MIL) brings his hands forward slightly prior to marginal contact occurring with Tatum's (BOS) side during the drive.
Brown (BOS) brings his forearm toward Lillard's (MIL) right side and marginal contact occurs as Lillard gathers the ball.
Beasley (MIL) brings his hands forward toward Tatum's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs with Tatum's front/side during the drive.
Porzingis (BOS) jumps forward slightly as he pursues the rebound and marginal body contact occurs with Connaughton (MIL) when Porzingis retrieves the ball.
Portis (MIL) extends his hand forward prior to marginal contact occurring with Porzingis' (BOS) back during Porzingis' upward shooting motion.
Lillard (MIL) releases his right hand away from Horford's (BOS) side and marginal contact occurs as Lillard steps back toward the perimeter.
Horford (BOS) legally contests Lillard's (MIL) jump shot attempt.
Beasley (MIL) and Tatum (BOS) engage and disengage with one another off-ball. Beasley then cleanly deflects the ball away from Tatum as the pass is made.
Middleton (MIL) brings his left hand outward prior to marginal contact occurring with White's (BOS) front as White starts his drive.

Connaughton (MIL) cleanly deflects the loose ball toward the perimeter prior to marginal contact occurring with White's (BOS) head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Beasley (MIL) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
There is no clear and conclusive video evidence determining if Lillard (MIL) makes contact with White's (BOS) left arm after his gather.
White (BOS) extends both arms forward and initiates contact with Portis' (MIL) upper body as Portis gathers the ball.
Beasley (MIL) wraps Brown's (BOS) upper body and initiates further contact with Brown's (BOS) back as the pass is made.
Brown (BOS) jumps forward slightly prior to marginal body contact occurring with Lillard (MIL) during Lillard's driving shot attempt.
Middleton (MIL) commits a take foul on Tatum (BOS). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Lopez (MIL) establishes himself in Brown's (BOS) path and does not deliver illegal contact as he sets the pick.
White (BOS) commits a take foul on Middleton (MIL).
Middleton (MIL) and Tatum (BOS) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Middleton (MIL) commits a take foul on Tatum (BOS). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Pritchard (BOS) legally contests Lillard's (MIL) jump shot attempt.
